output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who studied in each region five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HE providers, 2020/21 tax year.
output.maptext: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry five years after graduation, the region where the most graduates had studied was London. The regions where the fewest graduates had studied were East Midlands, East of England and South East. The region where the highest number of graduates lived five years after graduation was London.
output.maptext2: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the region with the smallest proportionate decrease in graduates who studied compared to living in the region five years after graduation was London, where the number of graduates decreased by -33.3%. The regions with the largest decrease were North East, North West, South West and West Midlands where the number of graduates decreased by -100%.
